				<h1 itemprop="headline" class="entry-title">Today in Small Business: A Positive Review on Yelp Goes Viral</h1>
		<div class="story-meta-footer">
			<address class="byline author vcard" itemprop="author creator" itemtype="//schema.org/Person">
				By Gene Marks			</address>
			<!-- date published --><time class="dateline " datetime="2014-09-24T16:10:05+00:00" itemprop="datePublished">September 24, 2014 12:10 pm</time>
			<!-- date updated --><span class="visually-hidden updated">September 24, 2014 12:10 pm</span><button class="button comments-button  theme-kicker" data-skip-to-para-id="">
</button>
		</div>
			</header>
		<div class="entry-content"><div id="sharetools-story" class="sharetools theme-classic sharetools-story" data-shares="email|Email,facebook|Share,twitter|Tweet,save|Save,show-all|More,ad" data-url="//boss.blogs.nytimes.com/2014/09/24/today-in-small-business-a-positive-review-on-yelp-goes-viral/" data-title="Today in Small Business: A Positive Review on Yelp Goes Viral" data-description="Why the fast-food industry is struggling. Why so many job postings are &quot;ridiculous.&quot; And do older workers impede entrepreneurship?">
				<div class="ad sharetools-inline-article-ad"></div>
				<div id="MiddleLeft" class="ad middle-left-ad nocontent robots-nocontent"></div>
				</div><div class="inlineModule"><div class="entry"><h6 class="kicker"><a href="//boss.blogs.nytimes.com/category/dashboard/">Dashboard</a></h6><p class="summary">A daily roundup of small-business developments.</p></div></div>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">Whatâs affecting me, my clients and other small-business owners today.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Economy<br />
</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>New <a href="//www.nytimes.com/reuters/2014/09/24/business/24reuters-usa-economy-housing.html">home sales</a> hit a six-year high.</li>
<li>The <a href="//www.businessinsider.com/shrinking-middle-class-takes-toll-2014-9">disappearing middle class</a> is a problem for the fast-food industry.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Employees</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>A start-up turns Googleâs famed <a href="//www.businessinsider.com/john-doerr-talks-betterworks-a-new-startup-that-shares-googles-employee-review-system-2014-9">employee review system</a> into an app.</li>
<li>Here&#8217;s why <a href="//www.forbes.com/sites/nextavenue/2014/09/22/why-so-many-job-postings-are-so-ridiculous/">so many job postings</a> are &#8220;ridiculous.&#8221;</li>
<li>Richard Branson says people <a href="//abcnews.go.com/Technology/richard-branson-lets-virgin-employees-unlimited-vacation/story?id=25696231">should be able</a> to take time off from work whenever they want and with no questions asked.</li>
<li>Does <a href="//goingconcern.com/post/why-your-firm-needs-bring-your-dog-work-policy">your company need</a> a bring-your-dog-to-work policy?</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Social Media</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Why a <a href="//www.customerserviceguru.co.uk/articles/review-pizza-express-go-viral">customerâs positive review</a> of a pizza restaurant went viral.</li>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"> <span id="more-88878"></span>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Entrepreneurship</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>A study from the National Bureau of Economic Research <a href="//www.nber.org/papers/w20506">claims that</a> &#8220;having too many older workers in society slows entrepreneurship.&#8221;</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Start-Up</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Start-ups are aiming at the <a href="//www.nytimes.com/2014/09/24/technology/24shave.html?ref=business&amp;smid=tw-nytimesbusiness">high-profit grooming industry</a>.</li>
<li>Two start-ups that <a href="//www.crainsnewyork.com/article/20140923/TECHNOLOGY/140929974/startups-to-allow-fans-greater-role-at-sports-events">help fans</a> take a greater role at sports events are merging.</li>
<li>A marketing start-up that helps businesses generate leads <a href="//on.recode.net/1uezbJu">gets nearly</a> $55 million in financing.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Finance</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>A <a href="//www.bizjournals.com/houston/blog/money-makers/2014/09/new-star-of-small-business-lending-in-houston-isn.html">new star</a> of small-business lending in Houston isn&#8217;t a bank.</li>
<li>Venture capital funding for <a href="//www.inc.com/jessica-stillman/good-news-vc-funding-for-female-founders-is-up.html">female founders</a> is up.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Cash Flow</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Here are five reasons to <a href="//blog.shoeboxed.com/5-reasons-check-cpa-year-round/9854/">check in</a> with your accountant year-round.</li>
<li>PayPal <a href="//thenextweb.com/insider/2014/09/23/paypal-integrates-bitcoin-processors-bitpay-coinbase-gocoin-merchants-us-canada/">is integrating</a> Bitcoin processors for merchants in the United States and Canada.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Management</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>General Motors is splitting Cadillac <a href="//www.nytimes.com/2014/09/24/business/gm-to-split-off-cadillac-and-move-brands-home-to-new-york.html">into its own business unit</a> and moving its headquarters to New Yorkâs trendy SoHo neighborhood.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Climate Change</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Forty companies sign a pledge <a href="//www.nytimes.com/2014/09/24/business/energy-environment/passing-the-baton-in-climate-change-efforts.html">to help reduce deforestation</a>.</li>
<li>The <a href="//www.nytimes.com/2014/09/24/business/economy/the-hidden-benefits-of-mitigating-climate-change.html">cost of curbing carbon emissions</a> may be cheaper than estimated &#8212; and it may even encourage economic growth.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Across the Country</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>A council member says agencies in Washington, are <a href="//www.washingtonpost.com/local/dc-politics/council-member-agency-says-dc-agencies-shortchanging-small-businesses/2014/09/23/1bc81748-429e-11e4-b437-1a7368204804_story.html">short-changing small businesses</a>.</li>
<li>More drought <a href="//www.insurancejournal.com/news/west/2014/09/23/341388.htm">is forecast</a> for the West.</li>
<li>A Washington state small-business loan program <a href="//www.bizjournals.com/seattle/morning_call/2014/09/washington-state-small-business-loan-program-lands.html">lands $31.5 million</a> in funding.</li>
<li>Rating service Fitch <a href="//online.wsj.com/articles/fitch-downgrades-pennsylvanias-bonds-by-a-notch-1411486374">downgrades Pennsylvania&#8217;s bonds</a>.</li>
<li>A business owner in Savannah, Ga., <a href="//businessinsavannah.com/bis/2014-09-23/broughton-business-owner-tussles-city-over-sign#.VCGXhyuSxZU">tussles with</a> his city over a sign.</li>
<li>Business owners in Seattle are <a href="//www.komonews.com/news/local/Business-owners-left-in-lurch-when-fashion-show-cancels-276418871.html">left in the lurch</a> when a fashion show cancels.</li>
<li>In Minnesota, police <a href="//www.twincities.com/breakingnews/ci_26588583/police-deliver-pie-after-pizza-hut-driver-hurt">deliver pizza after</a> a driver is hurt in a crash.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Around the World</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>London may be the worldâs <a href="//www.thetimes.co.uk/tto/life/property/article4216108.ece">most expensive city</a>.</li>
<li>A Chinese restaurant <a href="//theweek.com/speedreads/index/268643/speedreads-chinese-restaurant-admits-to-selling-opium-laced-noodles">admits to selling</a> âopium-laced noodles.â</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Marketing</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Matthew McConaughey&#8217;s<a href="//perezhilton.com/2014-09-22-matthew-mcconaugheys-odd-lincoln-car-commercial-gets-the-ellen-degeneres-treatment"> odd Lincoln Car Commercial</a> gets the Ellen DeGeneres treatment.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Taxes</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>How <a href="https://www.americanexpress.com/us/small-business/openforum/articles/how-establishing-a-foreign-presence-can-save-you-millions-in-taxes/">establishing a foreign presence</a> can save you millions in taxes &#8212; but new rules may make <a href="//dealbook.nytimes.com/2014/09/23/new-rules-make-inversions-less-lucrative-experts-say/">&#8220;inversions&#8221; less lucrative</a>.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Health Care</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>A small border town in Texas that used to be the most expensive place to get health care in the United States has been <a href="//www.nytimes.com/2014/09/24/opinion/a-health-care-success-story.html">transformed by the Affordable Care Act</a>.</li>
<li>Consumers will have a <a href="//www.nytimes.com/2014/09/24/us/under-affordable-care-act-25-percent-increase-in-health-insurers-is-predicted.html">broader selection of health insurance plans</a> in 2015.</li>
<li>This is a guide for individuals looking to <a href="//fitsmallbusiness.com/how-to-choose-health-insurance/#sthash.b7BynPyf.dpuf">choose and buy</a> health insurance.</li>
<li>Risks, regulations and cost pressures are <a href="//www.marketwired.com/press-release/ups-survey-time-to-act-on-untapped-opportunites-in-healthcare-industry-nyse-ups-1949955.htm">impeding healthcare executives</a> from seizing industry opportunities, according to a survey.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Ideas</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>A business suit âonesieâ <a href="//readwrite.com/2014/09/23/suitsy-business-onesie">is ingenious laziness</a> in clothing form.</li>
</ul>
